# Environment Variables Reference

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values.

```
# ==========================================
# DEVELOPMENT CONFIGURATION
# ==========================================

# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# ==========================================
# EMAIL CONFIGURATION (EmailJS)
# ==========================================

# Get these from https://www.emailjs.com
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# ==========================================
# ANALYTICS & TRACKING
# ==========================================

# Google Analytics (optional)
VITE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# ==========================================
# PAYMENT CONFIGURATION (Future)
# ==========================================

# Payment provider selection (disabled | razorpay | stripe)
PAYMENT_PROVIDER=disabled

# Razorpay (optional)
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY=

# Stripe (optional)
VITE_STRIPE_KEY=

# ==========================================
# BACKEND CONFIGURATION (Future)
# ==========================================

# Firebase (optional)
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=project.appspot.com

# Supabase (optional)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1xxxxxx

# ==========================================
# THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
# ==========================================

# Social Media URLs (optional)
VITE_INSTAGRAM_URL=https://instagram.com/your-handle
VITE_YOUTUBE_URL=https://youtube.com/@your-channel
VITE_TWITTER_URL=https://twitter.com/your-handle

# ==========================================
# FEATURE FLAGS
# ==========================================

VITE_ENABLE_3D_BACKGROUND=true
VITE_ENABLE_ANIMATIONS=true
VITE_ENABLE_STORE=false
VITE_ENABLE_BLOG=false

# ==========================================
# MAINTENANCE MODE
# ==========================================

VITE_MAINTENANCE_MODE=false

```

## Usage in Code

### Accessing Variables

```javascript
// Access environment variables
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL
const emailServiceId = import.meta.env.VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID

// Example usage
console.log(apiUrl) // http://localhost:3000
```

### In Configuration Files

```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default defineConfig({
  server: {
    proxy: {
      '/api': import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL
    }
  }
})
```

## Important Notes

⚠️ **Security:**
- Never commit `.env.local` to Git (it's in .gitignore)
- Use `.env.example` for template
- Keep sensitive keys private
- Rotate keys regularly
- Use different keys for dev and production

## Setup by Platform

### Local Development
1. Create `.env.local` in project root
2. Add variables from this file
3. Restart dev server to load changes

### Vercel
1. Go to Project Settings → Environment Variables
2. Add each variable
3. Select environments (Production/Preview/Development)
4. Redeploy

### Netlify
1. Site Settings → Build & Deploy → Environment
2. Add variables
3. Trigger new deploy

### Heroku
1. App Settings → Config Vars
2. Add environment variables
3. Dyno restarts automatically

### Traditional Hosting
Create `.env.local` in project root (same as local)

## Service Setup Guides

### EmailJS
```
1. Sign up at https://www.emailjs.com
2. Create email service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
3. Create email template
4. Copy Service ID, Template ID, Public Key
5. Add to environment variables
```

### Razorpay
```
1. Create account at https://razorpay.com
2. Get API Key from Settings → API Keys
3. Add to environment variables
```

### Firebase
```
1. Create project at https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Create web app
3. Copy config values
4. Add to environment variables
```

### Google Analytics
```
1. Create account at https://analytics.google.com
2. Get Measurement ID (format: G-XXXXXXXXXX)
3. Add to environment variables
```

## Verification

Test that environment variables are loaded:

```javascript
// Add this to your App.jsx temporarily
useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Env Variables:')
  console.log('API URL:', import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL)
  console.log('Email Service:', import.meta.env.VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID)
  // ... etc
}, [])
```

## Production Deployment Checklist

- [ ] All required variables set in production
- [ ] Sensitive keys use production credentials
- [ ] HTTPS enabled
- [ ] Analytics configured
- [ ] Error tracking enabled
- [ ] Email service tested
- [ ] Payment keys updated if using store
- [ ] Database connections verified
- [ ] API endpoints tested
- [ ] Third-party services tested

